    <Instrument_Host>
        <name>Venera 2</name>
        <type>Spacecraft</type>
        <description>

The Venera 2 spacecraft comprised a carrier bus holding a flyby module to
study Venus and interplanetary space during cruise. The bus was equipped
with TV imaging, spectrometers, particle detectors, micrometeoroid
detectors, magnetometer, and radio instruments. The flyby module had an
imaging system and three spectrometers. Communications failed before
flyby, returning only cruise data.

        </description>
